16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
18 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
19 A. The Oklahoma Legislature finds that:
20 1. To maintain strong economic growth and to improve the
21 quality of life of its citizens, the electrical generation capacity
22 within the State of Oklahoma must increase significantly over time;
23 2. Much of this required generation capacity will, by
24 necessity, be provided by renewable energy projects that have a
Req. No. 11595 Page 1

1 sign ificant footprint which could potentially impact agriculture
2 production;
3 3. There are strategies for both the siting and construction of
4 these renewable energy projects that could minimize this impact on
5 farming and ranching and in some cases assist in improving overall
6 agriculture productivity; and
7 4. It is in the interest of the public that the State of
8 Oklahoma develop a legislative strategy designed to encourage
9 renewable energy development in a way that works in harmony with
10 farming and ranching.
11 B. It is the intent of the Legislature that policies designed
12 to provide for new renewable energy generation construction also
13 supports the agriculture industry to be developed in the future.
14 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 850 of Title 17, unless there is
16 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Oklahoma
18 Agrivoltaics Act".
19 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
20 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 851 of Title 17, unless there is
21 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
22 A. There is hereby created the Oklahoma Agrivoltaics Advisory
23 Committee. The Committee shall consist of the following seventeen
24 (17) members:
