1 1. The Secretary of Agriculture or designee;
2 2. The Secretary of Energy and Environment or designee;
3 3. The Director of the Oklahoma Conservation Commission or
4 designee;
5 4. The Director of the Oklahoma Department of Wildlife
6 Conservation or designee;
7 5. One member representing the Division of Agriculture at
8 Oklahoma State University, to be appointed by the Governor;
9 6. Two members representing Tribal Governments, to be appointed
10 by the President Pro-Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate;
11 7. Two members representing the renewable energy industry, to
12 be appointed by the President Pro-Tempore of the Oklahoma State
13 Senate;
14 8. Two members who are producers of field crops, to be
15 appointed by the President Pro-Tempore of the Oklahoma State Senate;
16 9. Two members associated with the transmission and
17 distribution of electrical energy to be appointed by the Speaker of
18 the Oklahoma House of Representatives;
19 10. Two members who are producers of livestock, at least one of
20 whom is actively involved in range management, to be appointed by
21 the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of Representatives;
22 11. One member representing the Rural Utility Service of the
23 United States Department of Agriculture, to be appointed by the
24 Speaker of the Oklahoma House of Representatives; and
