1 12. One member representing the forestry industry, to be
2 appointed by the Speaker of the Oklahoma House of Representatives.
3 B. Members of the Committee shall serve without compensation
4 but shall be reimbursed for their actual and necessary expenses as
5 provided in the State Travel Reimbursement Act. The Oklahoma
6 Corporation Commission shall provide space for meetings of the
7 Committee and shall provide other assistance and staffing needs of
8 the Committee.
9 C. The Oklahoma Agrivoltaics Advisory Committee shall:
10 1. Advise and assist the Corporation Commission in preparing
11 any reports required by this section and in conducting the
12 assessment pursuant to Section 4 of this act;
13 2. Identify for Oklahoma agricultural and nonagricultural
14 landowners as well as renewable energy and transmission line
15 developers existing tools and government initiatives designed to
16 help in the siting and construction of renewable energy projects and
17 transmission systems in a manner supportive of farming, ranching,
18 and forestry, including agritourism and outdoor recreation leases;
19 3. Develop for consideration by the Oklahoma Legislature, the
20 Governor of the State of Oklahoma, the various Oklahoma state
21 agencies and the Oklahoma Congressional Delegation policy options
22 designed to encourage the development of renewable energy projects
23 and transmission systems in a manner supportive of farming,
